    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Oval boxes of light wooden-splint construction used to hold delicate finery or trinkets. Popular in the 18th and 19th century, bride's boxes were given as a marriage gift to brides to hold small items in the bride's trousseau such as linens, lace, and ribbons.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
